caption: This is quite possibly the best food I've ever had. The atmosphere is nice and the guy has a very grandfatherly and friendly vibe. I love this place!!! The spices and and everything were amazing and the location is super convenient.

We were so pleasantly surprised by the tasting meal. It gave us so many different flavors and chances to try things we may not have ordered on our own. It was our anniversary and we were visiting from New York and they went out of their way to make the whole night special. The manager and our waiter were so kind and really made us feel comfortable and welcome. Amazing meal.

Food was great! My wife had Chicken and Waffles. Had a nice spice and was "incredible".  Best chicken and Waffles. I had the Loaded Breakfast Biscuits.  They were great. Great tasting and very filling. Server was friendly but not very attentive after our food was served.

first time eating Ethiopian food the lentils were delicious the spices were perfect all the food was cooked to perfection. The lamb was delicious. I enjoyed drinking the Ethiopian beers. What a wonderful experience. We made a reservation about an hour before and the tables were ready and reserved for us when we got there. Half of our party hadn't arrived but they gave us no issues and seated us while we waited. When the rest of our party, they accommodated us and made us feel very comfortable even though we had a lot of kids. The food was amazing. Some of the best kitfo I've ever had. We were there for a while and they never once hassled us. They were very friendly and engaged us in conversation and we're great with the kids. We will definitely be back here for Ethiopian food when we're back in DC, and will definitely be suggesting this to friends coming to DC.

Some of the best food we've ever eaten, and easily the best Ethiopian.  The lentil sambusa came early and wowed our socks off with a perfect (not to oily) batter, and a lentil filling that was seasoned to make your mouth water. You see two of them in the photos because it's was so good, we had to order another, even before the other food came!  The meat Combo that followed exceeded every expectation we had, with perfectly cooked meats, amazing seasoning, enjera (Ethiopian bread) that was the perfect balance of soft/spongy/sour, and spice levels that made our mouths wake up and party.  We also loved the pictures in the restaurant, and the service was friendly, helpful, and attentive!
Enjoyed the mesir wet and Ethiopian beer.
The owner was very welcoming and we had a great conversation and then food was delicious!

We were in the area and went there attracted by the 5 star review. The food is DELICIOUS and not expensive (I had the vegetarian sampler). It is all made fresh so don't go there if you are in a rush. The waiter is super friendly and gives really good recommendations. I will go back again for sure. It is absolutely worth 5 stars.

I've been to over a dozen Ethiopian restaurants in the DC area and Shebelle is without a doubt the best one. The food is flavorful and cooked to perfection. The staff are lovely. The ambiance/decor is great. I have nothing but wonderful memories from this restaurant.

Wow! We just ate here tonight and I ran to my computer when we got home to review them because I want the world to know they have to eat here! Best Ethiopian we have had in DC, Denver and many parts of East Africa and by far the best service. The Veggie Sampler is flavorful, delicious and vegan friendly. The lentil sambusas were bigger than usual, extremely fresh and had a great spice level. Its also extremely affordable and to top it off they served a great new Ethippian beer we hadn't heard of - Negus! We will be back.

Husband and I happened upon Shebelle after 10pm on a Saturday night, when the neighborhood was jumping. The service, food, and decor were a calm respite to the electric vibe outside. We, like other reviewers, let our server pick the meats on our platter, and discovered some things we really enjoyed and didn't know before (wish I knew their names). The yellow lentils and cabbage were phenomenal. Can't wait to go back with the kids, who love Ethopian.

Best Ethiopian food in the area. Everything is fresh and tastes AMAZING. The service is great as well. The owner is very inviting and has amazing customer service as well all the rest of the staff. But above all the food is absolutely amazing. The decor is beautiful as well and the place is super clean. If anyone rates this place below a 5 they don’t know what they are talking about. Best Ethiopian spot! Highly recommend it.

Food was good, service was pleasant, but there were several issues: first of all, nearly everything has the same set of seasonings (onion and jalepeno among other things) and they don't have much of an indication of what's spicy and what isn't, so if you don't like spicy food and/or peppers, this is not the place for you. The other issue is the menu itself. I went with my parents, and their menus had different descriptions of the dishes than mine did, but the same dish names listed, which made it practically impossible to know what we were actually ordering. The drinks menus were also inconsistent, with one having about twice as many beer options than the other, many of which they didn't actually have. We also ended up just ordering what the waitress directed rather than what we had picked for ourselves, so it's a little hard to know how the other food would have been. At any rate, we ended up having a perfectly good meal, but not without considerable confusion and uncertainty.

What a wonderful new restaurant! The injera has the perfect consistency, the sambusas are to die for, and the veggie sampler was a delicious experience. The service was warm and considerate and the setting is colorful and reminiscent of home in the best of ways.

This is the best Ethiopian food I've ever eaten - every bite was delicious.  Staff was incredibly warm and lovely, and the artwork on the walls provides a vibrant and beautiful aesthetic too.  They serve a delicious Ethiopian beer called Negus that every beer lover should try!  Highly recommend this restaurant!

This is the best Ethiopian food I've ever had! Our server (the owner, if I'm not mistaken) was very friendly, cheerful, and helpful. I had the meat sampler with veggies and let him pick all of them for me. Every bite was delicious. Very good variety. He also introduced me to one of my new favorite beers--Negus--an Ethiopian craft beer. I have to find a liquor store that keeps Negus in stock! Smooth and well balances lager.

ABSOLUTELY AMAZING experience, food was great, service is impeccable. Overall great vibes and ambience. Beautiful decorations with paintings from Ethiopia. Had the yebeg kikil with njera, the broth was to die for and the lamb was well seasoned and tender. Would return!!!
This is definitely the place I will be going when missing my mom’s cooking. That’s how good and authentic the food is. Will highly highly recommend the doro wot and yebeg Kikil!!!

This might be my new favorite Ethiopian restaurant. We split two entrees, veggie platter and shiro, between 4 people and still had food to spare.  The misr wat wasn't as hot as I'm accustomed to, but the fragrant spice blend made it just as delicious. Even basics like the salad vegetables had a tangy twist and a few slices of jalapeño to keep my interest.  The owner had a tough time understanding our English, but he was very patient and helpful. He even stopped outside to ask if we needed directions when we were looking around.  I'm definitely keeping this in mind next time I need lunch on the green line.

Flavorful, delicious, and the owner was really nice.  We ordered the lentil sambusa, the vegetarian platter and the shiro; the vegetarian platter had more variety than most Ethiopian restaurants' platters, portions were huge, the shiro was rich, and the sambusa was fresh and flavorful.  We went here by accident but would go again.
